The paper deals with natural language interfaces to databases, which involves natural language processing (NLP) and machine learning (ML) techniques. Therefore, cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also discusses the use of a large dataset for training neural networks, which falls under cs.DB (Databases). The use of ML techniques for NLIDBs also suggests cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning) as likely sub-categories. Finally, the paper also mentions information retrieval (IR) techniques, which could place it under cs.IR (Information Retrieval).
